{"lemma":"قَبْضُ","slug":"قَبْضُ","root":"ق.ب.ض","root_slug":"ق-ب-ض","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ب-ض","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"قَبْض","root":"قبض","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":18},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n35099","n35100"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B6%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to seize, to take, to grab"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to take hold of, to take possession of"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hold"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to arrest"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to receive, to collect"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to collect, to gather"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to contract, to constrict"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to constipate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to oppress, to deject, to dishearten"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to contract, to constrict"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to give into (someone's) possession"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pay (a price)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of قَبَضَ (qabaḍa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"taking possession, possession"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"confiscation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"constipation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"receipt of a sum"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"suppression of the fifth letter of a foot when it is quiescent"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew קבץ (kaváts, “to collect, to gather”)."},"ipa":["/qa.ba.dˤa/","/qab.ba.dˤa/","/qabdˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35099","headword_ar":"قَبْضٌ","root":"qbD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking, taking with the hand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grasping; clutching; seizing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking possession of;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"receiving."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb.) ―         -b2-  And [hence],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Possession;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDapN","text_ar":"قَبْضَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, Mgh, Msb, TA:) or the latter is a n. un. [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an act of taking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking with the hand; a grasp; a seizure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAra Al$~aYo'u fiY","text_ar":"صَارَ الشَّىْءُ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDika","text_ar":"قَبْضِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDatika","text_ar":"قَبْضَتِكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thing became in thy possession."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi Ald~aAru fiY qaboDiY","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ الدَّارُ فِى قَبْضِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDatiY","text_ar":"قَبْضَتِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This house is in my possession;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;) like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY yadaY","text_ar":"فِى يَدَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Mgh","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n35100","headword_ar":"قَبَضٌ","root":"qbD","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqobuwDN","text_ar":"مَقْبُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadamN","text_ar":"هَدَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mahoduwmN","text_ar":"مَهْدُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafaDN","text_ar":"نَفَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manofuwDN","text_ar":"مَنْفُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is taken, of articles of property"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is collected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taken and collected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of spoils, before they are divided."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Mgh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala maAlu fulaAnK fiY AlqabaDi","text_ar":"دَخَلَ مَالُ فُلَانٍ فِى القَبَضِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The property of such a one entered into what was taken of the articles of property of the people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iToraHahu fiY","text_ar":"اـِطْرَحَهُ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqabaDi","text_ar":"القَبَضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Throw thou it among the things that have been taken:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) said to Saad Ibn-Abee- Wakkás, when he slew Sa'eed Ibn-El-'Ás, and took his sword: so in a trad. (TA.) And in another trad. it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juEila salomaAnu EalaY qabaDK","text_ar":"جُعِلَ سَلْمَانُ عَلَى قَبَضٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Selmán was set over spoils that were taken and yet undivided,"},{"kind":"text","text":"to guard and divide them. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Lth","Mgh","A"]}]}}